            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-field-body field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__item"><h3><strong>Picnic at the Estate</strong></h3>
<p>August 17, 2025 from 1 pm to 4 pm (with entry at 1 pm or 1:30 pm, as selected at the time of registration). &nbsp;<br>
Cost: $40 (plus tax) per person&nbsp;<br>
Ages 18 and up. &nbsp;<br>
<a href="https://anc.ca.apm.activecommunities.com/ottawa/activity/search?locale=en-US&amp;activity_select_param=2&amp;activity_keyword=Picnic%20at%20the%20Estate&amp;viewMode=list">Advance registration is required</a>. *Registration closes Thursday, August 14 at 5 pm.</p>
<p>Enjoy a Victorian-themed afternoon with friends and family. Picnic in style on the beautiful grounds at Billings Estate National Historic Site while enjoying a delicious lunch prepared by the tearoom kitchen. Experience activities inspired by popular pastimes of the period including lawn games and plein air art. Learn the secret language of fans and pose for a photographic memento inspired by the carte-de-visite. Guests are encouraged to dress to impress in their 19<sup>th</sup> century best!&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p>Each picnic meal includes a scone served with jam and Devon cream, two half sandwiches, two desserts, and refreshments (including a mocktail station). Picnic blankets will be provided. Admission to the museum is included.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<h4><strong>Notes</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li><span>The primary language of delivery for this program is English. Any printed materials will be provided in both official languages (English/French). &nbsp;</span></li>
<li><span>Advance registration is required. Registration is non-refundable and non-transferable.</span></li>
<li><span>We will make all reasonable attempts to accommodate allergy or dietary restrictions but are unable to ensure an environment free from all risk of cross-contamination and cannot guarantee the availability of menu alternatives. If you have questions regarding the menu, please contact <a href="mailto:museums@ottawa.ca" target="_blank">museums@ottawa.ca</a> in advance of the picnic.</span></li>
<li><span>The picnic and activities take place outdoors on the museum grounds. Check the forecast and dress for weather conditions. Sunscreen and bug spray are recommended. In the case of inclement weather, a decision may be made to cancel the event, and all registered participants will be contacted with further information regarding their options.  &nbsp;</span></li>
<li><span>The museum grounds include gravel, grassy, and uneven terrain. If you have questions regarding accessibility, contact the museum at 613-580-2088 or <a href="mailto:museums@ottawa.ca" target="_blank">museums@ottawa.ca</a>. Additional information regarding accessibility is available on the museum webpage.</span></li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
